		"description": "<p>Starting at 10th level, when you take damage, you&nbsp;can use your reaction to exploit chaos to protect&nbsp;yourself.</p><p>Roll 3d6 and check the individual values of the dice on the following table:</p><table style=\"width: 100%; height: 100.781px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 22.8083%;\"><col style=\"width: 77.1917%;\"></colgroup><tbody><tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\"><td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\"><strong>Result</strong></td><td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\"><strong>Effect</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height: 33.5938px;\"><td style=\"height: 33.5938px;\">distinct values</td><td style=\"height: 33.5938px;\">You reduce the amount of damage by the&nbsp;result of the highest dice, plus your&nbsp;spellcasting modifier (minimum 1).</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 33.5938px;\"><td style=\"height: 33.5938px;\">2 of a kind</td><td style=\"height: 33.5938px;\">You take half damage, and your assailant&nbsp;takes the other half of the damage.</td></tr><tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\"><td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">3 of a kind</td><td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">Your assailant takes that damage instead,&nbsp;and you take no damage.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Additionally, you gain temporary hit points equals to the highest die. Those temporary hit points last for 1 minute.</p><p>Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a short or long rest.</p>",
